members.name: URIInaccessible
members.comment: Indicates that the printer cannot access the URI address. For example, the printer might report this error if it goes to get the print data and cannot even establish a connection to the URI address.

members.name: URISchemeNotSupported
members.comment: Indicates that the printer does not support the URI scheme ("http", "ftp", etc.) in the URI address.

members.name: URIOtherProblem
members.comment: Indicates any kind of problem not specifically identified by the other reasons.

return: the URI that is the cause of this exception

members.name: getReason
members.comment: Returns the reason of this exception.

return: one of the predefined reasons enumerated in this interface

name: javax.print.URIException
comment: Interface URIException is a mixin interface which a subclass of PrintException can implement to report an error condition involving a URI address. The Print Service API does not define any print exception classes that implement interface URIException, that being left to the Print Service implementor's discretion.
